{
  "info": {
    "name": "Athena Import Lifecycle API",
    "description": "Focused lifecycle test collection for video imports: create → get status → list → cancel → retry.\n\n## Lifecycle Covered\n\n1. **Create Import** — submit a URL for import, receive import job ID\n2. **Get Import Status** — poll individual import job\n3. **List Imports** — list all import jobs with pagination\n4. **List My Imports** — list imports for authenticated user\n5. **Cancel Import** — cancel a pending/in-progress import\n6. **Retry Import** — retry a failed import\n7. **Error paths** — auth failures, quota exceeded, SSRF blocked\n\n## Note on Import Processing\n\nImports run asynchronously via goroutine. In a live test environment, poll `GET /api/v1/videos/imports/{id}` until status changes from `pending` to `processing` or `completed`. This collection validates the API contract; actual processing depends on server configuration.\n\n## Environment Variables Required\n\n- `baseUrl` - API base URL\n- `access_token` - JWT access token\n\n## Variables Set During Run\n\n- `import_job_id` - ID of the created import job",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Create Import",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Import - Valid URL",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 201, 400, 401, or 429', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect([201, 400, 401, 429]).to.include(pm.response.code);",
                  "});",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.test('Import job created with required fields', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('id');",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('source_url');",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('status');",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('created_at');",
                  "  });",
                  "  pm.test('Initial status is pending', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(body.status).to.equal('pending');",
                  "  });",
                  "  pm.environment.set('import_job_id', body.id);",
                  "  console.log('Import job ID:', body.id);",
                  "} else if (pm.response.code === 400) {",
                  "  console.log('400 - likely SSRF or validation rejection');",
                  "} else if (pm.response.code === 429) {",
                  "  console.log('Rate limited - 10 imports/minute');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}", "type": "text" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"targetUrl\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dQw4w9WgXcQ\",\n  \"video\": {\n    \"name\": \"Postman Test Import\",\n    \"privacy\": 1,\n    \"description\": \"Imported via Postman test\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/videos/imports",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "videos", "imports"]
            },
            "description": "Create a new video import job from a URL."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Import - Missing URL (400)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 400', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.equal(400);",
                  "});",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Error response present', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(body.success).to.be.false;",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('error');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}", "type": "text" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"video\": {\"name\": \"No URL import\"}}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/videos/imports",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "videos", "imports"]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
